<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=3>
<a name="10"><p><b>-Definition of a raid / Raid rules-</b></p></a>
</font>

<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2><p>
Raids are scheduled or spontaneous events involving 18 or more guildmembers. Officer participation is not necessary to define a raid. Standard farming of gear and/or EXPing is in no way a raid.</p>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="20"><p><b>-Earning Points-</b></p></a>

<ol>
<li>Each encounter will be pointed. Points will be given on a per major mob encounter. Victory is not necessary to gain points, it's the effort that counts<br><br>
<li>First time encounters and first kill encounters will received bonus points for 4x standard point values for first time encounter and 2x first time encounters for first kill encounters.<br><br>
<li>A list of points per mob is available<br><br>
<li>At the beginning of certain raids, we will take an "on time" log. People that are on time to that raid will receive bonus points. This will not be announced ahead of time and will not be included in every raid.<br><br>
<li>Raid values are structured with mundane, boring raids worth more points to encourage participation. All raids are all or nothing for that particular mob. Leeway will be given for longer raids.<br><br>
</font>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>


<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=3>
<a name="40"><li> <b>General Loot Policy</b><br><br></a>
</font>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
a)	Highest point total gets the item if there are more that one claim by users.<br><br>
b)	Points for the current raid are not applied until after that raid is completed.<br><br>
c)	JC Gems and money items will be collected during the raid. Please pay attention for who to give these items to at the raids.<br><br>
d)	Spells will be dictatored among interested guildmembers, not claimed<br><br>
e)	All point values are listed on the item list and are subject to change at any time.<br><br>
f)	No Drop items will be allowed to rot if they are not claimed.<br><br>
g)	Item turn in for "refund points" will be allowed per the discretion of the loot officers/GM.<br><br>
h)	You may at no time Sell/Trade/or Twink an item that is obtained via the points until all main guildchar's have equivelent or better items or are specifically cleared by the loot officers/GM to do so.<br><br>
i)	You may claim anything you wish as long as your class is listed as a user.<br><br>
j)	You may also claim anything for your twink/alt as long as no main characters claim an item. Mains ALWAYS have priority over alts reguardless of point totals.<br><br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="50"><li> <b>Guild vault</b></a> - We have created a guild vault. Items to be placed in the vault are as follows: <br><br>
a)	Cash from items and/or left over cash, to be use only for guild functions/items needed.<br><br>
b)	Droppable items that are not claimed by users (will be explained later)<br><br>
c)	The vault officer will compile a bi-weekly list of items/cash in the vault.<br><br>
d)	Valuted items may be sold if they are in the vault for more then 2 weeks for guild funds<br><br>
e)	We will entertain user and non-user claims from the vault at anytime after the raid where the item drops. Users still have priority.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="60"><li> <b>Droppable items change</b>:<br><br></a>
All droppable items that are not claimed by users at the time of the raid will go into the vault. The items may be claimed by users from the vault at any time thereafter. If, after 2 weeks, the items are not claimed by users (all users in the guild and who normally raid with us will be given the opportunity to claim) they may be sold.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="70"><li> <b>No Drop Items</b>:<br><br></a>
a)	Any no drop item not claimed will rot. There will be no freebies. This is not absolute and is at the discretion of the officers present.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="80"><li> <b>ToV Armor Quest Items</b>:<br><br></a>
a)	All ToV armor quest items will be dictatored.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="90"><li> <b>Alts</b>:<br><br></a>
a)	Alts DO NOT earn points for raiding. All points are tallied under the players main character.<br><br>
b)	Mains can claim items for their alts from their point pool.<br><br>
c)	Non-users may only claim for their one GUILDED twink at the raid.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="100"><li> <b>Going Negative</b>:<br><br></a>
a)	You can have your points go negative.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="110"><li> <b>Point values/list</b><br><br></a>
a)	This list will be posted seperately.<br><br>
b)	This list is subject to change at any time.<br><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<a name="120"><li> <b>Vetos</b><br><br></a>
a)	Loot Officers may veto any claim.<br><br>
b)	There will be NO discussion during the raid if a claim is vetoed, it simply wont be discussed in guild chat, ooc, whatever. If there are concerns, it can be brought up in guildchat or the boards at a later time.<br><br>

</ol>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=3>
<a name="130"><p><b>Points adjustments</b>:</p></a>
</font>

<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
On a weekly basis, a points adjstment equal to the total amount of points in (# of people at the raid * points for the raid) minus points out (Total of all items claimed) divided by all active members will be applied to all active members.<br><br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Example: Total value of points in for raids = 104.2<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Total value of points out for claims = 89.6<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Total # of active members = 90<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjustment = (89.6 - 104.2) / 90 = .1622<br><br>

This number is subtracted from every active member's total for that week to combat points inflation. It also encourages people to attend raids, attend the parts of raids that normally wouldn't drop loot (Planes clearings, Defender, Ring war, etc) as well as slowly errodes a person's total that is inactive.<br><br>



